primary_outcome.description:
major angiographic recurrence of the lesion or the presence of a residual aneurysm at last angiographic follow-up, as determined by the core laboratory, blinded to treatment allocation;
retreatment of the same aneurysm by endovascular or surgical means during the 18-month follow-up period;
an intracranial bleeding episode, or the occurrence or progression of a mass effect in relation to the treated aneurysm during the follow-up period, as determined by the blinded Adverse Event Committee.

